content: Little more challenging then most of the games I play. Graphic are great and the game keeps me interested.
Love ittt.

The gameplay was good but first time play I had to uninstall the game due to the slide viewer had  disappeared from the game. No problem with the operation of the game. Storyline was interesting. Morphs was too small and slow to find so I am disappointed  that I didn't get any acheivements  for that. Overall  great game

Not as good as number 3 the story was a bit weak and game play didn't always flow. The puzzles were good and they kept the HOS interesting. It was a good length and includes bonus chapter. I was spoilt with final cut homage so didn't like this as much but it's still a great game and above par. Worth a go if you love these games. Eipix are brilliant at what they do.
Very fun, great variety of puzzles and mini games, challenging without being too difficult. Fun continuation of the Final Cut storyline. Always love the Eipix games!

This is a solid game. It wasn't quite as good as the others in the series,  but it's certainly worth checking out. The game play hours are decent and the puzzles have some complexity and depth to them.
Fantastic game

Not my favorite game. For some reason I didn't find this game as enjoyable as the others in this series. I found myself bored while playing. A few minor glitches, skipped most if the mini games some due frustration others due to poor instructions. Not even going to bother playing the bonus game. Hope this is the end of the final cut sagas.
Very good HOG. Only negative is the game really for tablet. To small for a phone.  Some areas will not enlarge like the puzzle in a puzzle. Great graphics and sound. Would recommend to friends.
Enjoyable

Got halfway through the game, then my slide viewer disappeared! I tried everything (restarting device, etc) and nothing worked. I can't go any farther without being able to use the slide viewer so I had to uninstall and now I have to start all over. Up until then it was 5 stars, now it's a 1. If I get through it this time with no problems I'll update my review.
Keep them coming.
Exactly what I expected from this series
T truly enjoyed this game.... at times I had a hard time fining some hidden items; all in all it was fun!
Great graphics with mini puzzles different from what I have played ,before I really enjoyed them , all around great game.
A worthy sequel of a great game
The letters are too small to read as usual, but love their games.
Another great game!  Thank you Bigfish!
Great game
I only had 1 minor glitch! Great game....now I can go to bed. ...lol

Enjoyed the game. Some glitchiness, but worth looking past it as it didn't happen often. Great graphics, fun puzzles altho I had to skip more than one due to frustration. Long game and long bonus game. Has everything you would expect in quality game...morphing objects, collectibles, interactive HOS, and map. Worth the purchase for me.
It's nice to know there are still some BFG series that launch with an enjoyable game that can be played through from start to finish with out freezing etc. Fun game play with bonus after completion.
Another great installment in the Final Cut series. Collectables, travel map, great puzzles, variety of HOGs, and a great story. Great game.

Enjoyed playing, had no problems with it.
Really good - engaging game and good story.
Love it

I liked it but did not love it. Same game play as the other's so nothing new but still worth playing.

I'm really disappointed in this game.  I bought the full version and have had nothing bit problems since.  1st I had to uninstall twice, 2nd when it does open it says unlock even though I have already paid for it and 3rd when it starts up there a three cut scenes playing at the same time and on the menu for options no words show up.  So if you are thinking about buying this game I would definitely wait until they do some major updates.  If they cannot get it fixed I would like a refund.                REVISED. .. once I installed it for the third time I haven't had any problems.  Actually it's a really great game.  It has a lot to offer, lots of puzzles and it's a long game been playing for several days now.
It wasn't nearly as good as the other 2 final cut, they should have kept the same format as the other 2

It was okay. Something about this series, though... everything is too small on my Galaxy S4. Not bad but not great. As always, I'm appreciative of the transporting map, the morphing objects, and the collectibles.

Not as good as Homage, but still good. Worth paying for.

Just getting started and don't want to put it down.  Thanks Big Fish for paying attention to your customers and providing us (for the most part) with good quality, interesting games.
No issues watsoever
Another brilliant game keep them coming

These games have everything we love most. The game description will tell you that it has hidden film strips, souvenir room, HO's swap for match-3, achievements, replayable games and puzzles and more. Hopefully it'll handle smoothly and involve us in another absorbing story - like its predecessors. Big Fish has come through for us again, and I'm a happy player! If there's more to tell you - I'll be back. 3/9/2016.
